{"id": "EUVD-2026-2267", "enisaUuid": "cbd8ab48-3c85-398f-ae62-4716613571a5", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu/mediatek: fix use-after-free on probe deferral\n\nThe driver is dropping the references taken to the larb devices during\nprobe after successful lookup as well as on errors. This can\npotentially lead to a use-after-free in case a larb device has not yet\nbeen bound to its driver so that the iommu driver probe defers.\n\nFix this by keeping the references as expected while the iommu driver is\nbound.", "datePublished": "2026-01-13T15:31:25", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-13T15:31:25", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-71071", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1ef70a0b104ae8011811f60bcfaa55ff49385171", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5c04217d06a1161aaf36267e9d971ab6f847d5a7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/896ec55da3b90bdb9fc04fedc17ad8c359b2eee5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/de83d4617f9fe059623e97acf7e1e10d209625b5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f6c08d3aa441bbc1956e9d65f1cbb89113a5aa8a"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-71071", "GHSA-m2f3-4p6h-4879"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "01659948-e675-3a28-9675-484e6dc441c9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.2"}, {"id": "036b27f4-5217-334a-9f10-46aeca4193b9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "51080de72e26771f0ed9d44982974279ccbc92b8"}, {"id": "2dd57dc9-41fe-3164-a429-0fdd19cccdc3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.120"}, {"id": "6fa07ba3-9aee-3710-bcc3-2955b389160c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8412e5dd24ffc8bc21a00bfaa0b80d4596cdc9da <896ec55da3b90bdb9fc04fedc17ad8c359b2eee5"}, {"id": "7b9065fb-f097-3eed-9c63-cd792eb33220", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "26593928564cf5b576ff05d3cbd958f57c9534bb <1ef70a0b104ae8011811f60bcfaa55ff49385171"}, {"id": "861e8eab-c1fa-331d-a094-22b80d7279de",